---
title: Sweet Heat Vegan Cauli Bowls with Cabbage-Carrot Rice & Pickled Cucumber
description: Saucy cauliflower is the star of this bowl, making it a perfect vegan dinner idea! Here, you’ll roast florets until crisp and golden, then coat them in a jammy, garlicky sweet-hot glaze. Nestle the saucy cauli over a steaming bowl of veggie-loaded rice with tangy pickled cukes on the side. This bowl’s got all the bold flavors you crave, without the meat: Witness the power of cauliflower!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/sweet-heat-vegan-cauli-bowls-1245db3e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/sweet-heat-vegan-cauli-bowls-63e26fef021c97aea90880f0-07744e9a.pdf
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 500 kcal
  fat: 13 g
  saturated fat: 2 g
  carbohydrates: 91 g
  sugar: 35 g
  protein: 8 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1200 mg
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/sweet-heat-vegan-cauli-bowls-63e26fef021c97aea90880f0
servings: 2
time required: 35 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve @mini cucumber{1} lengthwise; slice into ¼-inch-thick half-moons. Cut
@cauliflower florets{10%ounce} into bite-size pieces. Trim @scallions{2}; mince
whites and slice greens on a diagonal into ½-inch pieces. Peel and mince or
grate @ginger{1%thumb}. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine cucumber, @rice wine vinegar{5%teaspoon},
@sugar{1/4%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{}. Set aside to pickle.

> Add ½ tsp sugar for 4 servings.

Toss cauliflower on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp},
salt, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat. Add
scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until fragrant and softened,
~{1%minute}.

Add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a pinch of salt. Bring to a boil,
then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium pan{} over medium-high
heat. Add scallion greens; cook until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add @red cabbage and carrot mix{4%ounce}; cook, stirring occasionally, until
scallions are slightly charred and veggies are tender, ~{3-4%minutes}. Turn off
heat; transfer to a plate. Wipe out pan.

In a second small bowl, whisk together @cornstarch{1/2%tablespoon} and @cold
water{1/4%cup} until no lumps remain. Set aside.

> Use all the cornstarch and ½ cup cold water for 4 servings.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium heat. Add ginger and
garlic; cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in @apricot jam{1%unit}, @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, cornstarch
mixture, and as much @sriracha{1%teaspoon} as you like. Cook, stirring
constantly, until thickened and syrupy, ~{2-3%minutes}. Reduce heat to low.

> Add water a splash at a time if sauce seems too thick.

When cauliflower is done roasting, add to pan with sauce; stir until thoroughly
coated.

Stir cabbage mixture into pot with rice.

Divide rice between shallow bowls. Top with saucy cauliflower and pickled
cucumber (draining first). Serve.